description:
This is a 11 minute workout called 'YOGA FOR LOWER BACK PAIN + TIGHTNESS ~Gentle Beginner Friendly Yoga Stretches For Back Pain(10 mins)' from the channel Tana Yoga.
The workout falls under Flexibility/Yoga and Flexibility/Stretching.
It's suitable for Beginner fitness levels.
The workout has a The Zen Flow and The Reboot Workout vibe.
The technique difficulty is Beginner.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: Hello Yogis! this gentle, beginner friendly lower back focused practice will help you ease some of the tension/ tightness you might  experiencing as we slowly lengthen our spine & hips. You can always come back to this simple practice whenever you need. If your'e sitting a lot this is also a great practice to come back to in the evenings. Hope this helps let me know how you go!
